ENTRY            E2828   20260227   20260508   20260508       E157
SUBENT        E2828001   20260227   20260508   20260508       E157
BIB                 12         38
TITLE      First extraction of the matter radius of 132Sn via
           proton elastic scattering at 200 MeV/mucleon
AUTHOR     (Y.Hijikata, J.Zenihiro, S.Terashima, Y.Matsuda,
            H.Sakaguchi, P.Arthuis, T.Miyagi, S.Ota, H.Baba,
            S.Chebotaryov, M.Dozono, T.Furuno, T.Harada,
            C.Iwamoto, T.Kawabata, M.Kobayashi, A.J.Krasznahorkay,
            S.Leblond, T.Lokotko, Y.Maeda, S.Masuoka,
            M.Matsushita, S.Michimasa, E.Milman, T.Murakami,
            H.Nasu, J.Okamoto, S.Sakaguchi, M.Takaki, K.Taniue,
            H.Tokieda, M.Tsumura, O.Wieland, Y.Yamaguchi,
            Z.H.Yang, R.Yokoyama, T.Uesaka)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNIPC,2JPNKTO,3CPRIMP,2JPNOSA,2JPNKON,2JPNTOH,
           2FR PAR,2GERTHD,2GERGSI,2JPNTSU,2JPNTOK,3KORKNU,
           3HUNDEB,3HKGUHK,2JPNMZK,2JPNKYU,2ITYMIL,3CPRBJG)
           (2JPNJPN) Department of Applied Physics, University of
                     Fukui, Fukui
           (2JPNJPN) Department of Physics, Toho University,
                     Funabashi
REFERENCE  (J,PTEP,2026,013D02,2026)
           Main reference. See also TITLE and AUTHOR.
           (T,HIJIKATA,2025) Y. Hijikata, Doctoral Dissertation
INC-SOURCE (FRAGM) A primary 238U beam at 345 MeV/nucleon was
                   bombarded on a 4-mm-thick 9Be target.
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
METHOD     (EDE)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNIPC) RIBF
DETECTOR   (MWDC,SCIN,NAICR)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The tracking efficiency of the recoil drift
                   chamber (about 2%)
           (DATA-ERR) The main components of the errors of the
                      cross sections in the forward and backward
                      angular regions are the ambiguity of the
                      solid hydrogen target thickness and the
                      statistical uncertainty, respectively.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Y.Hijikata+,J,PTEP,2026,013D02,2026) Fig. 5
HISTORY    (20260226C) MA
           (20260227R) Received by e-mail from Dr. Y. Hijikata.
ENDBIB              38
COMMON               3          3
EN-MIN     EN-MAX     ERR-1
